    <activity xml:id="activity-limits-analytically1">
        <statement>
            <p>Recall that in activity 2.5 we used numerical methods and table of values to find the limit of a degree 3 polynomial at a point. This was inefficient, “there’s gotta be a better way!”</p>

            <p>Given <m>f(x)=3x^2-\frac{1}{2}x+4</m>, evaluate <m>f(2)</m> and approximate <m>\lim_{x\to2}f(x)</m> numerically. What can we most definitively state?</p>
            <ol>
                <li><m>\lim_{x \to 2}f(x)=f(2)</m></li>
                <li><m>\lim_{x \to 2}f(x) \approx f(2)</m></li>
                <li><m>\lim_{x \to 2}f(x) \neq f(2)</m></li>
            </ol>
        </statement>
    </activity>
